snippet.textDisplay:
Malcom,

I started listening to you after one of my friends showed me your music in 2011. Back then, we use to longboard everyday and I would listen to nothing but your music when we did that. As you grew, your music was always there for me through breakups, depression, and anything else I went through. I lost my grandma last year to cancer, and only your music could help me through that grieving process, and still does. The day you died, apart of my childhood and soul died with you.

Rest easy, we love and miss you.
